{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the UK inheritance tax gift allowance in line with the US",
        "additional_details": "So that UK residents can give larger lifetime gifts without inheritance tax implications \u2014 aligned more closely with the US annual exclusion of ~$19,000 per recipient. We believe this would help families support loved ones during their lives and modernise UK tax policy.",
        "background": "We call on the UK Government to reform the current inheritance tax gift rules (where only \u00a33,000 is exempt each tax year before the seven-year rule applies)",
